# Walkthrough - Dolnytsky Typikon Rubrical Audit Remediation

## Executive Summary
This session successfully concludes the rigorous visual rubrical audit and structural remediation of **Part 3 (Menaion)** of the Dolnytsky Typikon through the end of August. By cross-referencing the digital English text directly against primary physical scans of the authoritative 2010 Lviv edition (Images 143-146), we resolved all textual drift, synchronized footnote anchors, excised trailing artifacts, and established continuous, highly durable repository tracking.

## Completed Changes

### 1. Menaion Liturgical & Structural Synchronization
In `Final_Dolnytsky_part3_menaion.txt`, several granular, high-fidelity restorations were made to align precisely with the 2010 Lviv source text:
- **July 31 Matins Sessional Hymn**: Corrected the rubric to specify the Sessional hymn is *"of the Cross"* (Хреста) instead of *"of the Forefeast"*, properly linking anchor `[^452]`.
- **July 31/August 1 Weekday Liturgy Restoration**: Restored the comprehensive Liturgy instructions detailing the Troparia, Prokeimenon, Apostle, Gospel, and Communion Hymns (*"Znamenovasya"* and *"Raduitesya"*), along with the complete rubrics governing the joint blessing of water and herbs following dismissal, tied to anchor `[^453]`.
- **July 31 Sunday Rule**: Restored the missing authoritative sentence governing the Bringing Out of the Cross, its veneration, and the blessing of water on Sunday, linked to anchor `[^451]`.
- **Excise of Trailing Bloat**: Completely purged the massive, redundant block of duplicate footnotes (`[^279]` through `[^465]`) appended after the August 31 entry, restoring clean structural boundaries to Part 3.

